# Siili Chatbot Widget — Project Rules

Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root for full project context, file map, design tokens, and common tasks.

## Styling

- ALWAYS use CSS custom properties from `src/styles/variables.css`. Never hardcode colors, spacing, or font families.
- Use CSS Modules (`.module.css`) for component styles. One module per component.
- Class names in CSS Modules should be camelCase.
- Border radius is `var(--radius)` (20px) on all interactive elements.

## Components

- All component files are PascalCase `.tsx` in `src/components/`.
- Each component file starts with a JSDoc block explaining what it renders, its props, and which widget mode it belongs to.
- Props interfaces are defined in the same file, not exported separately (types shared across components go in `src/types/index.ts`).

## Chat Service

- The mock service is in `src/services/chatService.ts`. It implements the `ChatService` interface from `src/types/index.ts`.
- When swapping for a real API, create a new file and update the import in `App.tsx`. Do not modify the interface.

## TypeScript

- Strict mode. No `any` types.
- Use `.ts` extension imports explicitly (e.g., `import type { ChatMessage } from '../types/index.ts'`).

## Design Reference

- Figma (screens): https://www.figma.com/design/0xXdKUlBJIolF15MjJuaMC/IR-site — `fileKey = 0xXdKUlBJIolF15MjJuaMC`. Use for screen-level composition (hero page, AI-agent page, loading state).
- Figma (design system): https://www.figma.com/design/rlh00CEImhMWwdRNOUqW6L/IR-DS — `fileKey = rlh00CEImhMWwdRNOUqW6L`. Use for component-level work (Textarea, Question+Answer, Reference tag, etc.). Code Connect mappings live here. See `AGENTS.md` §Figma for the node-ID table of both files.
- Font: Everett (Regular, Bold, Light). Assumed to be loaded by the host page.

## Figma-first workflow (visual changes)

- Before editing anything under `src/styles/**` or `src/components/**`, call `get_design_context` on the relevant Figma node(s). Find the node IDs in `AGENTS.md` §Figma and in `ACCEPTANCE_CRITERIA.md` §2.5 (Figma Manifest).
- Never invent visual values (colours, spacing, font sizes, radii). If Figma and the current implementation disagree, Figma wins — update the token in `src/styles/variables.css` and/or the component, not the node.
- In the change summary (commit message / PR description), list every Figma node ID you consulted, prefixed with the file (`site:` for IR-site screens, `ds:` for IR-DS components) — e.g. `Figma: ds:152:129, ds:152:116`. Reviewers and the sync job rely on this trail.
- After a visual change is merged, bump the `Last checked` / `Checked by` columns for the affected rows in `ACCEPTANCE_CRITERIA.md` §2.5.
- For broader drift checks, use the reusable prompt at `scripts/prompts/figma-sync.md` (scoped per PR, full-sweep weekly / pre-release). That prompt is read-only; applying its fixes is a separate turn.
